Differences in dyeing behavior of the samples were determined by a competitive dyeing process where all samples were dyed simultaneously in the same bath. Several dyes were tested. The dye selected and the application conditions were as follows:


Disperse Blue S-2GRL 200%, 0.1% ofw;

pH 6;

Bath ratio 1/20; and

Dyeing process


Step 1: initial temperature = 40℃; final temperature = 60℃ at 3℃/min;

Step 2: initial temperature = 60℃; final temperature = 115℃ at 1℃/min;

Step 3: isothermal at 115℃ for 45 minutes; and

Step 4: cooling until 60℃.

After dyeing, the samples were washed with sodium hydrosulphite (2 g/L) and sodium carbonate (1.5 g/L), at 60℃ for fifteen minutes. Chromatic coordinates and color differences were determined on dyed substrates. Dyeing exhaustion was obtained by an ultraviolet (UV) spectrophotometer, Shimadzu UV 1700. Chromatic coordinates and color differences were measured in a reflection spectrophotometer Minolta 3600 and calculated according to the CIE L*a*b* color space (CIELAB) formula.
